<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; }
    .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
    .warning-box { background-color: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; border-radius: 4px; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; }
    .stats { background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 20px 0; }
    .stat-item { margin: 10px 0; }
    .stat-label { font-weight: bold; }
    .footer { margin-top: 30px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; font-size: 12px; color: #666; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h2>⚠️ Exchange Rate API Usage Warning</h2>

    <div class="warning-box">
      <p><strong>Your Open Exchange Rates API usage has reached <%= @percentage %>% of the monthly free tier limit.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <p>Hello <%= @user.first_name.presence || 'Admin' %>,</p>

    <p>This is an automated notification to inform you that your application's exchange rate API usage is approaching the monthly limit.</p>

    <div class="stats">
      <div class="stat-item">
        <span class="stat-label">Current Usage:</span> <%= @usage.requests_count %> / <%= ExchangeRateUsage::FREE_TIER_LIMIT %> requests
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <span class="stat-label">Percentage Used:</span> <%= @percentage %>%
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <span class="stat-label">Remaining Requests:</span> <%= @remaining %>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <span class="stat-label">Month:</span> <%= @usage.month.strftime('%B %Y') %>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <span class="stat-label">Last Updated:</span> <%= @usage.last_fetched_at&.strftime('%B %d, %Y at %I:%M %p') || 'N/A' %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>What happens if the limit is exceeded?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The system will stop fetching new exchange rates</li>
      <li>Existing cached rates will continue to be used</li>
      <li>Invoice creation will still work with the last known rates</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Recommended Actions:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Monitor your usage for the rest of the month</li>
      <li>Consider upgrading to a paid plan if you need more requests</li>
      <li>Review which currency pairs are actively being used</li>
      <li>The limit resets on the 1st of next month</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="footer">
      <p>This is an automated message from your Miru application.</p>
      <p>You're receiving this because you have admin privileges.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
